Mikayla Seymour started the Mifflin scoring with a beautifully served ball to Gigi Discala for Mifflin's opening goal.
Evie Stricker created a small space from a pass a pass from Gigi Discalla finding the back of the net from 25 yards out to give Mifflin a 2-0 lead
Jessica Angstadt found Mikayla Seymour on the right flank, Mikayla lofted a shot from 30 yards out into the far corner to extend Mifflin's lead to 3-0

Mifflin's backline of Sierra Hess, Payton Klopp, Nicole Crammer, Bridget Martin, Jessica Angstadt and Lipuo Seifrit only allowed 5 shots on goal. Their stingy defense allowed Mifflin to build their attack and start many counter attacks.
